{{unreferenced|date=August 2016}} {{EngvarB|date=October 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Infobox book | name = Chronicle of Malaysia | image = <!-- Commented out because image was deleted: [[Image:Chronicle-Cover-2.gif]] --> <!-- Fair use rationale on Image:Chronicle-Cover-2.gif --> | caption = Cover for ''Chronicle of Malaysia'' | editor = Philip Mathews | country = Malaysia | published = 2007 Editions Didier Millet | media_type = Hardback | pages = 384 }}
The '''''Chronicle of Malaysia''''' gives an account of [[Malaysia]] from January 1957 to 31 August 2007. Published in conjunction with the 50th anniversary of [[Hari Merdeka|Malaysian Independence]], this book provides an account of major news events that occurred during this 50-year period. It covers the events as they unfolded in an eye-witness manner as if they were newspaper stories written at that time. These key events include the raising of the [[Flag of Malaysia|Malayan flag]], the [[Malayan Emergency|Emergency]], the formation of Malaysia, [[May 13 Incident|the 1969 riots]], political upheavals, the [[Asian financial crisis#Malaysia|financial crisis]], [[Law of Malaysia|judicial cases of note]], [[Sport in Malaysia|sport events]], [[Culture of Malaysia|cultural developments]], and miscellaneous aspects of daily life.
The Chronicle was launched on 5 November 2007 by [[Prime Minister of Malaysia|Prime Minister]] [[Abdullah Ahmad Badawi]].
